{"priority": "major", "kind": "bug", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "release-tools", "full_name": "osrf/release-tools", "uuid": "{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/81/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/81.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/81/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/81/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools/issues/81/linuxbrew-now-requires-ruby-20"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/81/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "title": "Linuxbrew now requires ruby 2.0", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 1, "content": {"raw": "We have a couple jenkins jobs that use Linuxbrew to create and modify homebrew pull requests. Recently ([Aug 16](https://github.com/Linuxbrew/brew/commit/179ef2bf8cb1fb24622c917ea8d9a7cad70d5de5)), Linuxbrew was updated to require ruby 2 or higher. This has caused failures on jenkins, since our jenkins node is configured to use ruby 1.9:\r\n\r\n* http://build.osrfoundation.org/view/os_homebrew/job/generic-release-homebrew_pr_bottle_hash_updater/66/console", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>We have a couple jenkins jobs that use Linuxbrew to create and modify homebrew pull requests. Recently (<a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://github.com/Linuxbrew/brew/commit/179ef2bf8cb1fb24622c917ea8d9a7cad70d5de5\" rel=\"nofollow\">Aug 16</a>), Linuxbrew was updated to require ruby 2 or higher. This has caused failures on jenkins, since our jenkins node is configured to use ruby 1.9:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://build.osrfoundation.org/view/os_homebrew/job/generic-release-homebrew_pr_bottle_hash_updater/66/console\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">http://build.osrfoundation.org/view/os_homebrew/job/generic-release-homebrew_pr_bottle_hash_updater/66/console</a></li>\n</ul>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2016-09-13T22:35:52.706425+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-09-13T23:54:13.221544+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 81}